						               													<description>MTR Railway Journey is a card game which is published by Hong Kong Mass Transit Railway (MTR) company.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All cards are Hong Kong MTR stations. The cards are divided as 8 groups of different railway lines (3 short lines combined as one).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players get 7 cards in their hands and race to empty their hands.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In turns, players attempt to play cards by matching its color, number, or word to the topmost card on the discard pile. If unable to play, players draw a card from the draw pile, and if still unable to play, they pass their turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After player play a card, if he gets any card with the same number/action, he can play all of them within the same turn. &amp;#10;e.g. the last played card is a RED card, A can play a RED 2, BLUE 2, ORANGE 2 all together.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Card Types:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Number, all carry the names of a MTR stations. The number ranges from 1-13(the longest line) to 1-4 (the shortest one).&amp;#10;    Interchange Station, it belongs to 2 railway lines (colors) and change the game play direction.&amp;#10;    Stop, to skip the next plyer. The effect can be accumulated to stop several players.&amp;#10;    Notice (+3), make the next player draw 3 cards. Player can play other Notice or Railway Journey card to avoid the effect and accumulate the effect on the next player.&amp;#10;    Wild Changing Color, player select a new color for the next player.&amp;#10;    Railway Journey (+4), make the next player draw 4 cards. Player can play other Railway Journey card to avoid the effect and accumulate the effect on the next player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
